From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Inject deterministic noise into AudioBuffer output

Detection vector: Audio fingerprinting creates an AudioContext, generates
a specific oscillator signal through an AudioBuffer, and hashes the
float samples returned by getChannelData(). Different audio stacks
produce subtly different output due to hardware and driver differences.

This patch applies a per-seed scaling factor to AudioBuffer samples
at the platform audio layer, making each browser launch produce a
unique but consistent audio fingerprint.

Surface: audio
Closes: AudioContext fingerprinting

--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/audio/audio_destination.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/audio/audio_destination.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ void AudioDestination::Render(const AudioIOPosition& output_position,
+  // AgenticBrowser: apply deterministic sample scaling to the
+  // rendered audio buffer. The scaling factor is derived from
+  // --ab-audio-factor=<float> (default: 1.0, range 0.99999-1.00001).
+  // This is applied at the platform audio layer so no JS API override
+  // is visible to detection scripts.
+  if (ab_audio_factor_ != 1.0f) {
+    ApplyAudioNoise(output_bus, ab_audio_factor_);
+  }
